  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment is included. The package decision is recorded as Accepted; however, the Discretization error factor carries an achievedLevel of 1 against a requiredLevel of 3, and the Model form factor carries an achievedLevel of 2 against a requiredLevel of 4, both constituting unremediated shortfalls that rebut the acceptance decision (W-AR-02).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-req",
